00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:34,399
And his job is to like improve user engagement and retention.

177
00:11:34,399 --> 00:11:40,000
And so he's in this exploratory phase trying to figure out like how do I drive more of that type of activity.

178
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:46,079
And what he observes is that 80% of people that review their games actually do so after a win.

179
00:11:46,079 --> 00:11:50,240
And that's really counterintuitive to when we initially built the feature.

180
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:56,399
We thought that people would want to use it after losses or to see their mistakes such they could like work on their mistakes.

